This paper discusses the challenges and implications of using social media and user-generated content in journalistic work, which involves aspects of computational social science (cs.CY) such as analyzing social media data and verifying its authenticity. The paper also discusses the design of tools to support journalistic work, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper touches upon information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of verifying the veracity of social media content. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CY and cs.SI, followed by cs.IR, cs.MM, and cs.HC.
